The paper proposes a new approach in iris recognition, which involves image segmentation and statistical encoding. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of statistical encoding also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of false accept rate, which is a security concern and could be relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
